A web chat client streams an LLM response over SSE. These are the controlling lines:
  const timeoutId = setTimeout(() => abortController.abort(), 120000); // armed when the request is sent
  function clearResponseTimeout() { if (cleared) return; cleared = true; clearTimeout(timeoutId); }
  // inside the SSE read loop, runs once per streamed event:
  if (event.delta) { clearResponseTimeout(); render(event.delta); }
Does this 120000 ms (2-minute) timeout bound (A) the total time for the whole completion, or (B) only the time until the first streamed token? Explain from the code.
